1. Clarity: The aim of the experiment is clearly stated and easy to understand. (5 point)
2. Relevance: The aim of the experiment is relevant to the tasks that follow and the overall topic of the report. (5 point)
3. Specificity: The aim of the experiment is specific and includes clear details about what will be accomplished in the tasks. (5 point)
4. Feasibility: The aim of the experiment is feasible given the resources and constraints of the report. (5 point)
5. Outcome: The aim of the experiment clearly states the expected outcome of the tasks. (5 point)


Note: The grading criteria is provided as a general guidance and can be adjusted based on the specific requirements of the task.